---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const demoUrl = 'https://demo.poesis.cloud';
const azureUrl = 'https://azuremarketplace.microsoft.com';
const repos = [
  { href: 'https://github.com/poesis-cloud/itip-web-frontend', label: 'itip-web-frontend' },
  { href: 'https://github.com/poesis-cloud/itip-web-backend', label: 'itip-web-backend' },
  { href: 'https://github.com/poesis-cloud/itip-definition-blackboard-repository-sourcer', label: 'itip-definition-blackboard-repository-sourcer' },
];
---
<BaseLayout
  title="ITIP"
  description="ITIP — the IT Intelligence Platform: the first domain application built on SIE, governing the IT landscape as a single, machine-operable source of truth."
>
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="eyebrow">Application</p>
      <h1>The IT Intelligence Platform.</h1>
      <p class="lead">ITIP is where every IT profile converges — architects, developers, ops, project managers, security and compliance — to define, govern, and visualize the IT landscape through a single governed source of truth. It is the first domain application built on <a href="/sie">SIE</a>, translating the <a href="/standard">GSM</a> standard for the IT domain.</p>
      <div class="hero-cta">
        <a class="btn btn-primary" href={demoUrl}>Try now</a>
        <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="https://docs.poesis.cloud/itip/">Read the docs</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section--soft">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="eyebrow">Why it matters</p>
      <h2>From governance that drifts to a model that maintains itself.</h2>
      <div class="grid grid-2" style="margin-top:1.5rem">
        <div class="card card--feature">
          <h3>Governance that stops drifting.</h3>
          <p>Architecture wikis, compliance spreadsheets, and review boards drift from reality the moment they are written. ITIP makes the <em>definition</em> the living source of truth — sourced from the real system, governed continuously, and never reconstructed under audit pressure.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card card--feature">
          <h3>A source of truth AI can act on.</h3>
          <p>Every definition is typed by a GSM Archetype, so its meaning is explicit and machine-readable. Humans and AI agents reason and generate from the same governed account of what your systems <em>are</em>, what they <em>must</em> do, and <em>why</em>.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="hero-cta" style="margin-top:1.5rem">
        <a class="btn btn-primary" href={demoUrl}>Try now</a>
        <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="https://docs.poesis.cloud/itip/">Read the docs</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="eyebrow">What it does</p>
      <h2>Four functional components, one governed loop.</h2>
      <div class="grid grid-2" style="margin-top:1.5rem">
        <div class="card"><h3>Definition</h3><p>Architecture, dependencies, obligations, and constraints live as one governed inventory — a single source of truth, with impact you can trace through typed relations.</p><p style="margin-top:.6rem"><a href="#definition">Explore ↓</a></p></div>
        <div class="card"><h3>Truth sourcing</h3><p>Code, API contracts, and infrastructure are sourced into governed definitions — so the model reflects reality instead of drifting from it.</p><p style="margin-top:.6rem"><a href="#truth-sourcing">Explore ↓</a></p></div>
        <div class="card"><h3>Frameworks</h3><p>TOGAF, ISO 25010 / 25012, GDPR, NIS2, DORA and more — sourced into ready-made Archetypes, Directives, and Norms you can enforce on day one.</p><p style="margin-top:.6rem"><a href="#frameworks">Explore ↓</a></p></div>
        <div class="card"><h3>Artifactory</h3><p>Generate any IT deliverable from the definitions — ADR packs, compliance evidence, architecture baselines, roadmaps — from Archetype-bound templates.</p><p style="margin-top:.6rem"><a href="#artifactory">Explore ↓</a></p></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="definition" class="section section--soft">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="eyebrow">Definition</p>
      <h2>One governed source of truth.</h2>
      <p class="lead">The definition inventory holds your Structures, Interactions, obligations, and constraints as governed, typed definitions — not wikis and spreadsheets. Because relations are typed, “if I change this, what breaks?” is answered by tracing the model, not by asking the longest-tenured engineer. It is the same object the BUILD and RUN layers reference.</p>
      <p><a href="https://docs.poesis.cloud/itip/general-usage/">Definitions in ITIP →</a></p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="truth-sourcing" class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="eyebrow">Truth sourcing</p>
      <h2>The model reflects reality, continuously.</h2>
      <p class="lead">ITIP sources IT artifacts — source code, API contracts, infrastructure — into governed GSM definitions through the SIE Blackboard, each contribution carrying a confidence score and a provenance envelope. The definition stays anchored to the real system instead of drifting from it.</p>
      <p><a href="https://docs.poesis.cloud/itip-blackboard-sourcer/">Truth sourcing in ITIP →</a></p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="frameworks" class="section section--soft">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="eyebrow">Frameworks</p>
      <h2>Adopt a framework — its governance is already in your model.</h2>
      <p class="lead">GSM's core is deliberately small; the domain meaning comes from <strong>Frameworks</strong> — established bodies of knowledge sourced into GSM as ready-made Archetypes, Directives, and Norms. TOGAF, ISO 25010 / 25012, GDPR, NIS2, DORA, SOC 2 and more — each enforceable the moment you attach it.</p>
      <div class="grid grid-2" style="margin-top:1.5rem">
        <div class="card"><h3>Governance, ready-made</h3><p>Directives and Norms encode the framework's requirements — enforceable on day one, not authored from scratch under audit pressure.</p></div>
        <div class="card"><h3>Meaning that travels</h3><p>Domain Archetypes carry vocabulary, grammar, and semantics together — so what “reliability” or “GDPR Article 32” requires lives in the type, not in someone's head.</p></div>
        <div class="card"><h3>They compose, not conflict</h3><p>Every framework speaks the same DNA, so a regulation, a quality model, and an architecture framework layer into one coherent fabric — overlaps merged, no silos.</p></div>
        <div class="card"><h3>Provable traceability</h3><p>Every Norm traces to the framework it came from, so regulatory coverage is continuous and provable — not reconstructed before each audit.</p></div>
      </div>
      <p style="margin-top:1.5rem"><a href="https://docs.poesis.cloud/itip/general-usage/">Frameworks in ITIP →</a></p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="artifactory" class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="eyebrow">Artifactory</p>
      <h2>Any IT deliverable, generated from the definitions.</h2>
      <p class="lead">The Artifactory turns governed definitions into operational IT deliverables — ADR packs, compliance evidence packs, architecture baselines, roadmaps, documentation — from Archetype-bound templates, each artifact traceable to the definitions it was built from. Generate from a single source instead of hand-authoring documents that are stale on delivery.</p>
      <p><a href="https://docs.poesis.cloud/itip/features/">The Artifactory →</a></p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section--soft">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="eyebrow">SaaS</p>
      <h2>Run ITIP as a managed cloud.</h2>
      <p class="lead">Operated by the team that builds it — start on the demo instance, or deploy from the Azure Marketplace.</p>
      <div class="hero-cta">
        <a class="btn btn-primary" href={demoUrl}>ITIP demo instance <span class="tag tag--muted">incoming</span></a>
        <a class="btn btn-ghost" href={azureUrl}>Azure Marketplace <span class="tag tag--muted">coming soon</span></a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="eyebrow">Build with us</p>
      <h2>Documentation &amp; source.</h2>
      <p class="lead">ITIP is part of the open Poesis stack.</p>
      <ul class="link-list">
        <li><a href="https://docs.poesis.cloud/itip/">ITIP documentation →</a></li>
        {repos.map((r) => <li><a href={r.href}>{r.label} →</a></li>)}
      </ul>
      <p style="margin-top:1.5rem" class="muted">Built on <a href="/sie">SIE</a> · implements the <a href="/standard">GSM</a> standard.</p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
